President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Mark Acton as Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission. Acton has been serving as a Commissioner on the Postal Regulatory Commission since 2006. He previously held positions as Special Assistant to the Chairman of the Postal Rate Commission and as Staff Director for the Republican National Committee Counsel's Office. Acton holds a B.A. from the University of Louisville and an M.B.A from the University of Maryland.